  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2, android.view.KeyEvent.Callback, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory2, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, android.view.Window.Callback, com.magnet.mobile.android.inject.spi.ViewContainer

    @Dynamic
@ExternalContracts(value=android.app.Activity.class)
public class MagnetActivity
extends android.app.Activity
implements com.magnet.mobile.android.inject.spi.ViewContainer
    Extended Activity to support Services startup and data injection. By default, implicit data injection takes place only after setContentView(int), setContentView(View) or setContentView(View, android.view.ViewGroup.LayoutParams). However, caller may explicitly do the data injection by calling initializeNow().

    Note, however, that if using InjectView for injected elements, care should be exercised when initializeNow() is called. If you need to call initializeNow() prior to setting the content view, then you should use Provider or Reference based injection. For example: 

       private @InjectView(R.id.someid) javax.inject.Provider<TextView> myTextView;
    Using this approach injection will succeed as a deferred operation. Once get() is called on the provider/reference, the injection point will be evaluated using findViewById().
